{{short description|2009 book by Christopher S. Hill}} {{Infobox book | name = Consciousness | author = [[Christopher S. Hill]] | image = Consciousness (book).jpg | subject = [[Consciousness]] | published = 2009 | publisher = [[Cambridge University Press]] | pages = 276 pp. | isbn = 9780521125215 }}
'''''Consciousness''''' is a 2009 book by [[Christopher S. Hill]] in which he offers explanations of six forms of [[consciousness]]: agent consciousness, propositional consciousness, introspective consciousness, relational consciousness, phenomenal consciousness, and experiential consciousness.<ref>{{cite web |title=Christopher Hill |url=https://www.brown.edu/academics/philosophy/index.php?q=christopher-hill |website=[[Brown University]] |accessdate=21 October 2018 |language=en}}</ref>
