'''Jean Jolivet''' (9 January 1925 – 8 March 2018) was a French philosopher and medievalist.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ephe.fr/actualites/deces-de-jean-jolivet |title=Décès de Jean Jolivet |date=2018-03-12 |website=École Pratique des Hautes Études |language=fr |access-date=2018-03-14}}</ref><ref>[https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&q=Jean+Jolivet+Abelard&btnG=Search&as_sdt=2000&as_ylo=&as_vis=0 Googlescholar, Jean Jolivet] (retrieved 10 January 2011)</ref>
Jolivet was an authority on Medieval philosophy and honorary director of studies at the [[École Pratique des Hautes Études]] in Paris. He is co-director of the publication series "Études de philosophie médiévale" (founded by [[Étienne Gilson]]) for the [[Vrin Library of philosophy]]. Jolivet has been an influential mentor for, and collaborator with, [[Constant Mews]], particularly in relation to [[Peter Abelard]].<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=8aGPhkxcqMMC&pg=PR9&lpg=PR9&dq=%22Jean+Jolivet%22+%22École+Pratique+des+Hautes+Études%22&source=bl&ots=FcFTSOs1EX&sig=T_kX2DzAULx18t1Y92O9tGHXdEw&hl=en&ei=BZIqTdS7AoGHnAen_6DuAQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=9&ved=0CFYQ6AEwCA#v=onepage&q&f=false Constant J. Mews, ''The Lost Love Letters of Heloise and Abelard: Perceptions of Dialogue in Twelfth Century France" Pelgrave, New York, 2001, p. ix] (retrieved 10 January 2011]</ref>
== Publications == Amongst Jolivet's publications are:<ref>[http://philpapers.org/s/Jean%20Jolivet Philpapers, Publications by Jean Jolivet] (retrieved 10 January 2011)</ref> *''Perspectives médiévales et arabes'', Vrin, 2006 * ''Le siècle de saint Bernard et Abélard'', Fayard, 1982 * ''La Théologie et les arabes'', Editions du Cerf, 2002 * ''La Théologie d'Abélard'', Editions du Cerf, 1997
